observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Local Chief Executive:
Instruct the Municipal Accountant to adequately observe the deadline set for the submission of trial balances and other financial reports as required under Paragraph 1, Section 122 of PD 1445 and Section 7.2.1a of COA Circular 2009-006;
Direct the Accounting Office to only accept claims, assign DV Numbers and process payables when supporting documents are complete;
Direct the Municipal Treasurer to require and maintain contact numbers of payee-suppliers and claimants to facilitate immediate release of checks to the latter;
Instruct the Municipal Accountant to submit the revenue and disbursement documents to the Audit Team until the 10th day of the following month, and
Cause the suspension of payment of the salaries of the employees responsible for the delayed submission or non-submission of the required reports until the same shall have been complied in pursuance with Paragraph 2 of Section 122 of PD 1445.

We recommended and the Municipal Mayor agreed to:
4.7.1 	require the Inventory Committee to complete the conduct of the physical count of PPE of the Municipality and  undertake all other procedures prescribed under COA Circular 2020-006 dated January 31, 2020;
4.7.2 	instruct the GSO and the Municipal Accountant to reconcile their records after the physical count and effect the necessary adjustments, if any;
4.7.3 	require the GSO to submit to the Auditor the RPCPPE as of December 31 not later than January 31 of the ensuing year, and
4.7.4 	instruct the GSO to undertake proper disposal of unserviceable properties, if any.

We recommended and Management agreed that the Municipal Mayor instruct the GSO to:
8.12.1	immediately work out for the issuance of red plates by the LTO for the four vehicles without plate numbers and install the same in front and at the rear of every vehicle/truck;
8.12.2	work out for the conversion of the five vehicles with private plates into red plates;
8.12.3	cause for the proper markings of all vehicles owned by the municipality as prescribed in COA Circular No. 77-61 to prevent unauthorized or improper use thereof, and
8.12.4	cause for the immediate registration of the vehicles with LTO and henceforth see to it that such registration is renewed before the expiration date.

We recommended and the Municipal Mayor agreed to require:
12.7.1 the Municipal Engineer to instruct all contractors to see to it that henceforth, all laborers are provided with complete and appropriate PPEs and cause for the installation of warning devices at the project site whenever necessary in order not to compromise the health and safety of the workers and the public, and henceforth indicate the actual percentage of completion of the pay items in the SWA;
12.7.2	the Municipal Accountant to carefully scrutinize the supporting documents of disbursement vouchers and determine with certainty the amount due to the contractors in order not to unduly benefit the latter at the expense of the municipality.

To correct the aforementioned deficiencies, we recommended that the Municipal Mayor:
15.6.1	instruct all the heads of offices to fill out all the data in the PR and indicate the exact unit of measure and complete specifications of items being requested to be purchased and avoid indicating the brand name except for replacement of parts;
15.6.2	instruct the GSO to see to it that all the data in the RFQ/Canvass Paper are completely filled out and that the exact unit of measure and complete specifications of items being canvassed are indicated therein except the brand name unless the items are replacements of parts;
15.6.3	instruct the GSO to require the bidders to indicate in the RFQ/Bill of Quantities the brand name of items they are quoting which shall be  incorporated in the PO;
15.6.4	instruct the GSO to see to it that all data in the PO are completely filled out and the exact unit of measure and complete specifications of items being ordered are indicated therein including the brand name of the items as indicated by the winning bidder in the RFQ/Canvass Paper/Bill of Quantities;
15.6.5 	instruct the Municipal Accountant and the GSO who sign the inspection and acceptance portions of the AIR respectively that such document is properly filled out and the exact unit of measure and complete specifications of items accepted and inspected including the brand name of the items  be indicated therein;
15.6.6 	require the Municipal Accountant to submit the lacking documents for the purchase of lot in order for the municipality to cause for the transfer of ownership from the previous owner to the name of the LGU;
15.6.7 	require the Municipal Accountant to submit the lacking documents of infrastructure projects with total gross amount of  ₱68,504,713.48 to avoid the issuance of Notices of Suspension;
15.6.8	require the GSO Designate that henceforth,  attach History of Repair  using the prescribed format indicating among others the  plate number and date of acquisition of the vehicle being repaired and  the dates and complete details of   all previous repairs undertaken including the current repair;
15.6.9  	require the Municipal Accountant to issue a certification that the previous cash advance of the payee has been liquidated before processing payment for another cash advance.
15.6.10	require the Municipal Accountant to see to it that cash advances for payroll are supported with payroll duly signed by the signatories indicated in Boxes A to D therein without the signatures of the payees, as basis of the amount to be cash advanced.  Likewise, see to it that cash advances for specific purpose/time bound undertaking be supported with breakdown of estimated expenditures;
15.6.11	instruct the Municipal Health Officer and the Municipal Accountant that henceforth, purchases of medicines be supported with Certificate of Product Registration, Certificate of Good Manufacturing Practice from FDA, Batch Release Certificate from FDA and Certification from the manufacturer that the supplier is an authorized distributor to ensure the safeness and effectives of the items purchased,  and
15.6.12	instruct the Municipal Accountant not to process claims for payment unless these are supported with complete documents.

We recommended that Municipal Mayor require the Municipal Accountant:
a. Locate source documents of the transactions included in the Other Payable account and inform the suppliers to present their corresponding claims duly supported with the required documents for processing and payment thereof; 
b. Locate the source documents and MOA/Trust Agreements with the source agencies and review the terms and conditions relative to the implementation of programs and projects. Determine the viability of the usage of funds and if the same could still be used for other projects, seek the approval of the source agencies if deemed necessary; 
c. Return/remit to the source agency any unused/unexpended balance if so stipulated in the MOA/Trust Agreement in order to reflect the correct balance of the account in the financial statements; 
d. Effect the transfer of funds which are due to other funds and prepare adjusting entries of long outstanding accounts; and 
e. Furnish COA with the JEV effecting the adjusting/correcting entries relative to the foregoing.

We recommended that Municipal Mayor require the Municipal Accountant:
Locate source documents of the transactions included in the Other Payable account and inform the suppliers to present their corresponding claims duly supported with the required documents for processing and payment thereof;
Locate the source documents and MOA/Trust Agreements with the source agencies and review the terms and conditions relative to the implementation of programs and projects.  Determine the viability of the usage of funds and if the same could still be used for other projects, seek the approval of the source agencies if deemed necessary;
Return/remit to the source agency any unused/unexpended balance if so stipulated in the MOA/Trust Agreement in order to reflect the correct balance of the account in the financial statements;
Effect the transfer of funds which are due to other funds and prepare adjusting entries of long outstanding accounts; and
Furnish COA with the JEV effecting the adjusting/correcting entries relative to the foregoing.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive;

a) Instruct the Engineering Office to Provide the Municipal Budeget Officer with copies of the Statement of Work Accomplished (SWA) of the above-mentioned on-going and completed as basis for the recording of obligations; and



b) Instruct the Municipal Accountant to cause the preparation of necessary journal entry to correct the understatements of Construction In Progress-Infrastructure Assets, Construction In Progress-Buildings and Other Structures and Accounts Payable by P15,991,001.49 P4,312,981.20 and P20,303,982.69, respectively.

observations.reason:
Contract review and evaluation showed Management’s compliance with the provisions of the procurement law except for few transactions where:
Notices to Proceed were not acknowledged by the successful bidders;
The estimated budgeted amount per APP differed with that of the PPMP;
Documents such as approved technical specification, and abstract of PhilGEPS posting were not attached;
The Notice of Award was posted at the  PhilGEPS website beyond the 3 days reglementary period.

The Bids and Awards Committee was reorganized.
